    <detaileddescription>
<para>The <bold>IADLXDesktopServices</bold> is the main interface for the Desktop domain and provides control to desktop specific functionality.</para>
<para><table rows="4" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="no"><para>InterfaceId:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>IADLXDesktopServices</para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Smart Pointer Interface Name:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>IADLXDesktopServicesPtr</para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Inherits:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para><ref refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x_interface" kindref="compound">IADLXInterface</ref></para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Inherited By:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A</para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
<para>The <bold>IADLXDesktopServices</bold> interface provides:<linebreak/>
 <ndash/> the list of desktops instantiated on the AMD GPUs.<linebreak/>
 <ndash/> the interface for registering and unregistering for notifications when the desktops are changed.<linebreak/>
 <ndash/> the interface for creating and destroying AMD Eyefinity desktops.<linebreak/>
</para>
<para><heading level="2">Methods </heading>
</para>
<para><table rows="5" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="yes"><para>Method   </para>
